perhaps white should wait a little to make this move, as the bishop could be harassed by Nh5 now. Bf4 is indeed a good move, though, and I didn't play Nh5.
Developing the queen and hitting e4. Looking back I think Nh5 is better.

A surprising move, indeed, but not a bad one. I think however, better for white is Nf3, or maybe Qc2. Both moves save e4 and give white good position. (If 8)Nf3 Nxe4 9)Qa5  wins a piece). Instead, the following moves leave black in an at least okay situation. I feel that white was better after my not so hot Qe7 move.
